<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="601" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/2674</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winslow</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-06-30"><hi rend="italic">June 30,
                                1927</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received July 6.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 2148</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the last sentence in the
                            penultimate paragraph of my despatch No. 2139 of June 27, 1927,<note n="17" xml:id="d601fn17">Not printed.</note> I have the honor to
                            transmit herewith a complete translation of the Constitutional Amendment
                                Bill<note n="17" xml:id="d601fn18">Not printed.</note> as it was
                            published in the <hi rend="italic">Gaceta Oficial</hi> of June 21.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">L. Lanier
                            Winslow</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>